name: Grandma McFlurry
summary: McDonald's is honoring grandmothers with the introduction of its limited-edition Grandma McFlurry. The sweet treat features vanilla soft serve blended with crushed Oreos and a sprinkle of sugar cookie pieces, reminiscent of homemade cookies often associated with grandmothers. The Grandma McFlurry is available for a limited time at participating McDonald's locations across the country. In New York City, the McFlurry is being given away for free at select locations.

name: Scottie Scheffler
summary: Scottie Scheffler, the world's top golfer, was arrested outside the PGA Championship venue in Louisville on Friday for allegedly assaulting a police officer. Despite his arrest, Scheffler returned to the tournament and played in the second round. A pedestrian was also killed after being hit by a shuttle bus outside the golf club. Scheffler released a statement after the incident. According to news reports, Scheffler was arrested early Friday morning after police responded to a disturbance call near the Valhalla Golf Club. He allegedly resisted arrest and assaulted an officer. Scheffler spent several hours in jail but was released in time to play in the second round of the championship. He climbed the leaderboard despite the arrest and finished the day tied for 10th place. The circumstances surrounding Scheffler's arrest are still under investigation.

name: Houston weather
summary: Severe weather has caused widespread damage in Houston, including power outages that could linger for weeks. A derecho with winds of up to 100 mph left over 1 million residents without power, while at least 7 people were killed. The storms also caused significant damage to buildings, including skyscrapers. Some areas may face weeks without power, and temperatures are expected to rise in the coming days. Officials are urging residents to stay safe and avoid downed power lines.

name: PGA Championship leaderboard
summary: The PGA Championship is underway, and Scottie Scheffler is leading the pack with a 9-under after Round 2. Xander Schauffele is close behind with a 6-under, while Collin Morikawa and Scottie Scheffler are tied for third at 5-under. Tiger Woods, who was arrested for assault of a police officer, is sitting 10 strokes back on the leaderboard. Min Woo Lee has made a significant move up the leaderboard with three chip-ins. The cut line is projected to be at 1-over, and some notable players, including Rory McIlroy and Justin Thomas, are in danger of missing it.

name: Young Sheldon
summary: The recent finale of the hit sitcom "Young Sheldon" has generated a lot of buzz. The episode featured surprise cameos from Jim Parsons and Mayim Bialik, who reprised their roles as adult Sheldon and Amy from the original series "The Big Bang Theory." The finale also marked the return of Reba McEntire, who plays Sheldon's grandmother. The episode saw a surge in viewership, reaching a four-year high. Showrunner Steve Molaro explained that the series finale will not be the funeral that fans have been speculating about. Despite the conclusion of the series, the prequel spinoff will continue, picking up where the finale left off.
